reviewText: Good book, good movie, wonderful cars!  Danielle never disappoints!
A great story about love of family!
Not to thrilled with this tape - when  I watched the first 10 minutes and then it decided to start flipping and it did not stop.

This has been one of my favorite movies for years and I am happy to finally own it.  Dramatic and touching, MUCH better than the book version.  Excellent acting, I just love Bruce Greenwood and Gabrielle Carteris! Also Bess Armstrong does an excellent job of portraying a grieving Mother.

Sometimes life throws us challenges and we, somehow over come these opsiksuls. This movie Tells a story of the hardships of deciding to have children. And sometime what couples have to do just to have a child of there own. Its a great move
